oc:kn_07c0c34a a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When reassessing ticket priority" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Automatically bump priority up when: SLA is breached, multiple customers report the same issue, customer explicitly escalates, workaround stops working, or issue expands in scope." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Escalation triggers prevent situations from silently worsening without intervention." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_0bc134a9 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During initial ticket analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Read the full ticket before categorizing — context in later messages often changes the assessment. Flag patterns — escalate the pattern even if individual tickets are low priority." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Partial reading leads to mis-categorization and missed systemic issues." .

oc:kn_243fb480 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating triage output" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Write internal notes that help the next person pick up context quickly. Include what you've already checked or ruled out to avoid duplicate investigation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Support handoffs are common; good internal notes reduce rework and improve resolution time." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_2be7ebd3 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining primary category" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Categorize by root cause, not just the symptom described. If the customer can't log in due to a bug, category is Bug (not Account)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Root-cause categorization ensures tickets reach the team that can actually fix the underlying problem." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_4f0539a0 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assigning P1-P4 priority to a ticket" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When in doubt on priority, err on the side of higher — it's easier to de-escalate than to recover from a missed SLA." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Under-prioritizing a serious issue causes more damage than briefly over-investing in a lower one." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_6ed7dd0a a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before routing any ticket" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never route a ticket without first checking for duplicates and known issues across the support platform, knowledge base, and project tracker." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Routing a duplicate creates parallel investigations, wastes resources, and fragments context." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_dff47592 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a ticket spans multiple categories" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If the customer reports both a bug and a feature request, the bug is primary. When in doubt on category, lean toward Bug — it's better to investigate than dismiss." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Bugs represent regressions or failures that are always higher urgency than feature requests or how-to questions." .

